name: IF I'D ID MY ID, I'D HIDE. IF I'D ID MY ID, I'D HIDE.
description: Translation: If I could identify my id (is the unconscious psychic intensity that works to satisfy basic urges, needs, and desires.) I would hide. Playing on the use of the various meaning of I'D/ID/ID/I'D we can make a minimal sentence that has maximal impact. (That sounds scary Andrew.) Well, it's the most animalistic aspects of our personalities and guess what, you all have it too. Don't forget, you're an animal, just like a cat, a crow, an orca, or a wolf. We all have a surface personality that's run by our ego, but deep down we're all animals. What separates us from the rest of animal kingdom? Is it our consciousness? Are we unique in having consciousness? Are dogs or other animals conscious? If we're just self-aware conscious animals, then wouldn't someone who has a deeper connection to their id, more of an ancient mindset? I don't have answers, just bringing up questions to ponder and think about.
